The paper deals with image classification and information retrieval, which are primarily related to computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The proposed framework also utilizes steganography for secure retrieval, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of ontology for mapping low-level features to high-level concepts is also related to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
